unittest-cpp
------------------------------------------
UnitTest++ is a lightweight unit testing framework for C++. It was designed to
do test-driven development on a wide variety of platforms. Simplicity,
portability, speed, and small footprint are all very important aspects of
UnitTest++. UnitTest++ is ANSI portable C++ and makes minimal use of advanced
library and languages features, which means it should be easily portable to
just about any platform.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.8.2-1
  libgcc1-6.3.0-2
  libstdc++6-6.3.0-2
  libUnitTest++-devel-2.0.0-1bl1
  libUnitTest++2-2.0.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.28-3
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-6.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-6.3.0-2
  libtool-2.4.6-4
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/unittest-cpp/unittest-cpp

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/unittest-cpp/unittest-cpp/archive/v2.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack unittest-cpp-2.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./unittest-cpp-2.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/unittest-cpp-2.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/unittest-cpp-2.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libUnitTest++2-2.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libUnitTest++-devel-2.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

